This place was surprisingly great! I thought it was going to be some corny chain but wow! The food was good...we got chicken enchiladas with fried beans and rice, Mole enchiladas and some beers.  The decor was so cool! Every detail is thought out. The place is brand new, clean, and there were interesting decorations all around. They also have tvs at both bars upstairs and downstairs....and even in the bathrooms.  The service was fantastic as well!! Loved this stop; it's a regular now.
